1. Compute base premiums for each item (with block handling for components)
2. Compute item-specific modifiers (cursed +50%, high enchantment +30%)
3. Sum all item base premiums → policy base premium
4. Apply policy-wide modifiers (loyalty -20%, first insurance +10%, follow-up -15%) to policy base premium
5. Total = sum of (item_base + item_modifiers) + policy-wide_modifiers + 5 fee
6. Round up

But the current test only needs base premiums + first insurance + fee. Let me implement just what's needed:

- Base premiums by type
- Component block handling (3 alike = 60 instead of 75)
- First insurance (10% of total base)
- Processing fee (5)
- Round up

